# Map rules

See `docs/MAP_CERTIFICATION.md` and `docs/PROTECTED_SYSTEMS.md` (RaceMapController, RaceMapDefinition, City Highway).

## Required

- New maps: prototype/test only until certified (`enabled=false` or `enabled_for_testing=true`).
- Every map: `RaceMapDefinition` `.tres` + scene contract (`RoadArena`, `CoreRoad`).
- Promotion to playable: pass `--tier=certification` and promotion checklist in MAP_CERTIFICATION.md.

## Banned unless explicitly requested

- Silent City Highway fallback in debug/headless.
- Competing finish triggers (`GoalCatch` emitting `zombie_reached_base`).
- Authoritative void kill zones (use `Zombie._check_out_of_bounds`).
- Map scene cameras hijacking spectator camera.
- `enabled=true` / playable status without certification.

## Tests

| Change | Run |
|--------|-----|
| Catalog / controller / definition | smoke + certification |
| Bridge layout / gameplay | + `--tier=map` or `broken_bridge_real_gameplay_test.gd --zombies=5 --skip-stress` |
| Docs only | none |

Fail loud: print map id and failed requirement. Never treat fallback City Highway as success.
